<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,310,1478,1504]" box="[189,310,1478,1504]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,1478,1504]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,1478,1504]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[189,1400,1525,1729]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
Recognized by the following characters: total body length 3.2–3.7; corium uniformly yellow, without dark pattern (
<figureCitation box="[350,446,1561,1587]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="44.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[233,1383,291,1835]" captionTargetId="figure-17@44.[189,1398,274,1854]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Fig. 3. Habitus of Mertila Distant, 1904 and Namyatovia gen. nov. spp. A–C. Mertila rubrocephala sp. nov., ♂, UASB. A. Dorsal view. B. Head and pronotum in dorsal view. C. Abdomen in ventral view. D–F. Namyatovia castlerockensis gen. et sp. nov., ♂, UASB. D. Dorsal view. E. Head and pronotum. F. Lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690368" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690368/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); antenna uniformly dark brown, usually with reddish tinge; right lateral wall of genital capsule deeply excavated, with large, apically rounded sclerotized outgrowth (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1387,1596,1622]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="62.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[245,1345,377,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-62@62.[189,1398,370,1890]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="Fig. 21. Male genitalia of Namyatovia castlerockensis gen. et sp. nov., paratype, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and right lateral views. C–D. Right paramere in dorsal and ventral views. E. Left paramere in dorsal view. F. Aedeagus lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690407/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 21A–B</figureCitation>
); right paramere flattened, with broadly semicircular dorsal expansion (
<figureCitation box="[1025,1172,1631,1658]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="62.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[245,1345,377,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-62@62.[189,1398,370,1890]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="Fig. 21. Male genitalia of Namyatovia castlerockensis gen. et sp. nov., paratype, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and right lateral views. C–D. Right paramere in dorsal and ventral views. E. Left paramere in dorsal view. F. Aedeagus lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690407/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 21C–D</figureCitation>
); base of aedeagus with large, characteristic, uniformly sclerotized outgrowth; apex of aedeagus with small, entirely membranous lobe (
<figureCitation box="[414,512,1702,1729]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="62.[189,232,1929,1955]" captionTargetBox="[245,1345,377,1884]" captionTargetId="figure-62@62.[189,1398,370,1890]" captionTargetPageId="62" captionText="Fig. 21. Male genitalia of Namyatovia castlerockensis gen. et sp. nov., paratype, UASB. A–B. Genital capsule in dorsal and right lateral views. C–D. Right paramere in dorsal and ventral views. E. Left paramere in dorsal view. F. Aedeagus lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690407" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690407/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig 21F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
